    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:24:"http://purl.org/atom/ns#";a:1:{s:4:"name";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"S. Abbas Raza";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2411:"<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>Jihad</strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">by Sir Mohammad Iqbal</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;"> </p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">"The pen is mightier than the sword,"<br> preaches an imam from the pulpit.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">In our era such sermons lack virtue: Don't<br> talk of a Muslim with a dagger, speak</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">instead of a Christian gunrunner who<br> smears a striving for truth as unholy.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Ask: If war is immoral for the East,<br> is it not so for the West, and if truth</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">is the path, why are Western blunders<br> burnished and those of Islam broadcast?</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;"> </p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Translated, from the original Urdu, by Rafiq Kathwari</p></div><div class="feedflare">
